      <article class="prose-shopify mt-14 max-w-4xl">
      <div><h2>Why this comparison matters</h2><p>For Drip vs Sendlane, drop orchestration with inventory truth separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ridge Run Coffee (subscription plus flash offers, $72k/mo) runs subscribers suppressed from flash promos; flash offers only to non-subscriber engaged segment. Operating lesson: Campaign collision audit caught flash SMS hitting active subscribers. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Drip vs Sendlane, bargain-hunter isolation from VIP access separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Cipher Audio (high-AOV headphones, $320k/mo) runs product launch calendar: teaser email week -2, launch sms to engaged browse-abandon only. Operating lesson: No launch discount — margin held at 58% vs 41% on prior discount launches. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Drip vs Sendlane, Sequenzy email depth beside Postscript SMS separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Patchwork Denim (upcycled fashion, $54k/mo) runs one-of-one pieces — sms for new listing drops only to style-preference segments. Operating lesson: Generic blasts had 0.3% conversion vs 4.1% for tailored drops. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p></div>
